AMD + CISD v12 — Smart Money Concept Strategy
📋 Description
AMD + CISD is a complete strategy based on Smart Money Concepts (ICT) that automatically detects Accumulation → Manipulation → Distribution cycles by combining volatility analysis (Bollinger Bands), volume profiling and institutional liquidity detection.
Unlike traditional AMD indicators relying on fixed session times, this strategy uses market structure itself to identify phases — making it universal across all markets (Crypto, Forex, Indices, Stocks) and all timeframes.

🔑 Core Concepts
Accumulation (A)
The market enters a compression phase: Bollinger Bands squeeze and volume drops. Price builds a tight range where liquidity accumulates on both sides — buy stops AND sell stops stack above and below the range.
Manipulation (M) — Liquidity Sweep
Price violently breaks out of the range with a volume spike to grab liquidity:

BSL (Buy Side Liquidity) 💧: Sweeps the highs — sellers' stops get triggered
SSL (Sell Side Liquidity) 💧: Sweeps the lows — buyers' stops get triggered

This is the institutional trap: the move lures retail traders into the wrong direction.
CISD (Change In State of Delivery)
The exact moment price reverses direction after manipulation. It's the break of the last opposing candle (the low of the last bullish candle for a bearish AMD, or the high of the last bearish candle for a bullish AMD). This is the entry trigger.
Distribution (D)
The real directional move begins — opposite to the manipulation. This is where smart money distributes positions and informed traders profit.

🔍 How It Works
Phase Detection

Bollinger Squeeze (bandwidth in lowest percentiles) → Accumulation phase detected
Breakout + Volume spike → Transition to Manipulation
Liquidity pool scan (BSL/SSL) via clustered swing highs/lows
Liquidity sweep confirmed 💧 → Manipulation validated
CISD detected (structure break) → Entry signal
Distribution → Trade active with TP/SL

Trading Signals
ModeDescriptionAggressiveImmediate entry on CISD confirmationPullbackEntry on CISD level retest with low volume — better R:RBothCombines both modes — double opportunity

🛡️ Smart Stop Loss (3 Modes)
The SL is the critical component of this strategy. Three modes available:
ModeLogicManip Zone (recommended)SL placed above/below the ENTIRE manipulation zone + ATR bufferStructureSL at the last significant swing high/low + bufferFixed ATRSL at fixed ATR distance from manipulation level
Additional Protections

Minimum SL Distance: SL is always at least 1 ATR from entry — prevents tight stops getting hunted
Configurable Buffer: Extra ATR buffer added to SL
Auto Breakeven 🔒: SL moves to entry price when trade reaches 1R profit
Trailing SL (optional): SL follows price at a set distance once in profit

CISD Invalidation

CISD is only invalidated if price closes beyond the level + an ATR buffer (not on a simple retest/wick)
Configurable option: invalidation can close the trade immediately OR let TP/SL manage the exit (recommended OFF)


💧 Liquidity Detection
The indicator automatically scans for institutional liquidity pools:

BSL (Buy Side Liquidity) 🔴: Cluster of swing highs at the same level — zone where sellers' stops are concentrated
SSL (Sell Side Liquidity) 🟢: Cluster of swing lows — zone where buyers' stops are concentrated
🔥 Strong Pool: Displayed when touch count exceeds the configured threshold
💧 SWEPT: Marked when price runs through a liquidity pool

The liquidity filter can be enabled to only allow signals when a BSL or SSL pool has actually been swept — significantly increases signal quality.

⏰ Killzones (Session Filter)
Optional filter to limit signals to the most active trading sessions:

London (02:00-05:00 UTC default)
New York (07:00-10:00 UTC default)
Asian (20:00-00:00 UTC default)
Configurable timezone (UTC, Paris, London, New York, Tokyo...)

AMD patterns are always drawn on chart, only trading signals are filtered.

📊 Dashboard & Debug
Dashboard (top right)

Current phase, direction, BSL/SSL status
Active SL mode + breakeven status
Backtest stats: Net P&L, Win Rate, Profit Factor, Max Drawdown

Debug Panel (bottom left)

Bandwidth percentile, squeeze count
BSL/SSL levels and sweep status
SL distance in ATR, CISD buffer
Trade count


⚙️ Recommended Settings
Getting Started

Squeeze: Threshold 30%, Min Duration 5, Lookback 60
High Volume: 1.3x average
SL Mode: Manip Zone, Buffer 0.5 ATR, Min 1 ATR
R:R: 2.0
Liquidity: Require sweep ON
CISD: Invalidation ON, Buffer 0.5 ATR, Close position OFF
Killzones: OFF to start, then enable to filter

Market-Specific Adjustments

Crypto: Increase squeeze threshold to 35-40%, SL buffer to 0.7 ATR
Forex: Default settings, enable London + NY killzones
Indices: Reduce bandwidth lookback to 40, squeeze min 3 bars


⚠️ Disclaimer
This indicator is a technical analysis tool and does not constitute financial advice. Past performance does not guarantee future results. Always backtest and paper trade before going live. Manage your risk responsibly.

🔄 Changelog

v12: Smart SL (3 modes), minimum distance, CISD buffer, BSL/SSL liquidity, killzones, breakeven, trailing
v10: Institutional liquidity detection added
v9: Backtest strategy() integrated
v4: Switched from fixed sessions to Bollinger/Volume detection
v1: AMD detection via fixed session times


